🧱 B01 — BLOCK 8 of 8 — Smoke test on a real record
This block does five things at once: creates a record, exercises Notes, exercises the alternate key, verifies audit captured the change, and reads the views back. If all five land cleanly, B01 flips to Done.

8.1 — Create the smoke-test Rule record
Where: open the Active Rules view → + New (top toolbar). The Main form opens.
Field values — copy each block:
Rule Name:
Smoke_R1_HostingTypeCloud_Applicable
Description:
Smoke test rule — applicability when hosting type is Cloud.
Conditions JSON:
{"op":"eq","field":"Application.pei_hostingtype","value":"Cloud"}
Plain-English Rendering:
When Application Hosting Type is Cloud, this control is Applicable.
Output:
Applicable
Collection Scope:
Per app — all
Priority:
10
Terminating:
No
Status:
Draft
Effective From: pick today's date at 00:00 (midnight). Most date-time pickers default to current time — clear it and set 12:00 AM if needed.
Effective To: leave blank.
Current Version:
1
Click Save (or Save & Close).

8.2 — Add a Note (verifies attachments work — this resolves the deferred Block 6 check)
After save, open the record (if it closed). Look for the Notes / Timeline / Related area on the form. Find + New note (or click into the Notes pane).
Note title (or just the body text):
Smoke test note — confirms attachments enabled on pei_rule.
Save the note.

8.3 — Trigger an audit entry by editing one field
In the open record, change Description to:
Smoke test rule — applicability when hosting type is Cloud. (edited)
Save.

8.4 — Open Audit History on the record
From the record form: Related tab → Audit History (or in the command bar: ⋯ → Related → Audit History).
You should see at minimum two audit entries:

A Create event (the initial save)
An Update event with Description field change captured (showing old value → new value)

If a third entry appears for the note creation, that's normal.

8.5 — Test the alternate key (uniqueness rejection) — answers the deferred B01-17
Open the Active Rules view OR All Rules view (the Draft record is in All Rules since the Active filter excludes Drafts). + New again. In the new form:
Rule Name (intentionally duplicate):
Smoke_R1_HostingTypeCloud_Applicable
Fill in the other required fields with anything (e.g., copy the same values from 8.1). Click Save.
Expected: Dataverse rejects the save with an error message containing words like "duplicate" / "alternate key" / "already exists". The exact wording varies, but the save MUST fail.
After confirming the rejection, cancel/discard the second record (don't try to bypass; don't save with a different name to "make it work"). The rejection IS the success state.

8.6 — View verification
Navigate to Active Rules view. Confirm:

Your smoke record does NOT appear (because Status=Draft, filter is Active-only).

Navigate to All Rules view. Confirm:

Your smoke record DOES appear with all the expected columns populated.
